<TITLE> Power failures hit much of the country </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 15 (bdnews24.com)  Much of the country is reeling from power failures as the national grid has run into technical glitches, an official with Bangladesh Power Development Board said Saturday. ASM Bazlul Haque, director (public relations) of BPDB, told bdnews24.com at 1:40pm: "Repair work is going on. We are trying to restore power supply as soon as possible." The power failures stemmed from the technical glitches at Ashuganj Power Station, which occurred at 11:45am. bdn
